article_title: Only 4 of 34 who voted against it remain.
article_text: In 2009, 34 House Democrats voted against the Affordable Care Act. Many came from red or purple states—Texas, Tennessee, Ohio—and identified themselves as part of the moderate-to-conservative "Blue Dog" coalition. (No Senate Dems voted against the bill.) Politico writes today that, despite voting against the most prominently liberal legislation of the past decade, few of them have been able to hang on to their seats in the ensuing Republican wave:
